I am not sure if this is a result of my MS, but sometime (specially when I feel warm) I quickly  start sweating and feel like all my body is itching. It can happen even in the winter time that I start sweating outside and this situation is not at all tolerable. I have to go somewhere and take off my jacket in order to dry my body and cool myself. Another symptom that I am not sure was included in the above questions is that sometimes when the weather is cold and I do not have enough warm clothes (let's say an evening summer), I start shaking immediately. This is a feeling that starts right in the middle of my spine and makes all my body shake like a vibration engine.
